ith more time.</p>\n\n<h3>They think you can pay now</h3>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> will expect you to pay immediately and take payment over the phone by direct debit, credit or debit card.</p>\n\n<p>If you can&rsquo;t do this, they&rsquo;ll tell you what other payment options you can use. </p>\n\n<h3>They think you can pay with more time</h3>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> may offer you extra time to pay if they think you genuinely can&rsquo;t pay in full now but will be able to pay in the future. </p>\n\n<p>They&rsquo;ll encourage you to set up a direct debit to make payments on dates they agree with you. They may agree for you to pay in instalments.</p>\n\n<p>If your circumstances change and you can pay your tax bill faster, you should tell <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> as soon as you can.</p>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll have to pay interest on the amount you pay late.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You must keep these payments up to date and pay your other tax. If you don’t, <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> will normally cancel the arrangement and take legal action against you straight away.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>They don&rsquo;t think you can get your payments up to date</h3>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> won’t make an arrangement with you - they&rsquo;ll expect you to pay your tax bill straight away. </p>\n\n<p>If you don’t, <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> will start <a href=\"/if-you-dont-pay-your-tax-bill\" title=\"If you don't pay your tax bill\">‘enforcement action’</a> to get the money from you.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You can pay <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> in different ways, including direct debit.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>You can get help and advice from <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/payinghmrc/problems/debt-help.ht