ns Tax</a> on the profit</li>\n  <li>is from overseas and UK tax must be paid on it</li>\n  <li>income is more than £100,000 a year</li>\n  <li>is taxable but HM Revenue &amp; Customs (<abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>) can&rsquo;t collect the tax through your tax code - eg you pay a higher rate of Income Tax and have savings or investments </li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Other reasons</h3>\n\n<p>Other reasons for sending a tax return include, you:  </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>are finalising the affairs of someone who’s died</li>\n  <li>are a trustee of a trust or a registered pension scheme</li>\n  <li>are a religious minister of any kind</li>\n  <li>pay tax through <abbr title=\"Pay As You Earn\">PAYE</abbr> but want to pay the tax you owe without changing your tax code</li>\n  <li>are employed and want to claim expenses or professional subscriptions of more than £2,500</li>\n  <li>claim Enterprise Investment Scheme or Venture Capital Trust relief</li>\n  <li>are a name or member of Lloyd’s of London insurance market</li>\n  <li>are over 65 and your income is over the <a href=\"/income-tax-rates\" title=\"Income Tax rates\">limit for an age-related allowance</a></li>\n  <li>have lived or worked abroad or you aren&rsquo;t <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/international/personal.htm\" title=\"Residence\">domiciled in the UK</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>Check with <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> if you don’t think you have to send a tax return.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Self Assessment Helpline</strong>  </p>\n\n<p>0845 900 0444<br />\nMonday to Friday, 8am to 8pm<br />\nSaturday, 8am to 4pm</p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/self-assessment-tax-returns/deadlines","slug":"deadlines","order":3,"title":"Deadlines","body":"<h2>Filing your tax return</h2>\n\n<p>The 2011 to 2012 tax year ended 5 April 2012. The main deadlines are:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>paper ta